Page2.Subtext: We are building on and improving Windows Admin Center, but we need your help to make sure it’s the best it can be. Click the link under the help section to send us feedback or suggestions. We look forward to hearing from you!

Page1.Subtext: Windows Admin Center is a new web-based management solution from Microsoft, built to modernize and simplify administration of your Windows datacenter.
Page1.Title: Welcome to Windows Admin Center

access.adSuccessMessage: Access Control has been successfully changed to Active Directory and local groups. Please refresh your browser for these changes to take effect.
access.aadSuccessMessage: ​Access Control has been successfully changed to Azure Active Directory. Please refresh your browser for these changes to take effect.
access.manageNote: ​If you have not completed the above steps, all members of the AAD tenant have gateway user access and only local administrators on the gateway machine have gateway administrator access.
access.manageGuide: To manage gateway user and gateway administrator access:
access.saveWarning: The gateway will be restarted when access control is changed. You must refresh your webpage for changes to take effect.
access.manageStep4: You can update access for the SME AAD application in the Azure portal at any time.
access.manageStep3: In the Users and groups tab, select 'Add user'. You must assign a gateway user or gateway administrator role for each user/group added.
access.manageStep2: In the Properties tab, set 'User assignment required' to Yes
access.manageStep1: Go to your SME AAD application in the Azure portal.
access.manageSubTitle: If you want to give specific AAD users or groups gateway user and gateway administrator access, you must do the following:
access.manageDesc: By default, all members of the AAD tenant will be gateway users. Only local administrators on the gateway machine will be gateway administrators.
access.connectStep2: Run New-AadApp.ps1 with this gateway name as the –GatewayEndpoint parameter. For example: New-AadApp.ps1 –GatewayEndpoint https://gateway.contoso.com
access.connectStep1: Download the New-AadApp.ps1 script from​ this .zip file

access.connectToGatewayDesc: To control access using Azure Active Directory, you must first connect your gateway to Azure. You will only need to do this once on this gateway.

access.addSecurityGroupMessage: Groups in which SME checks for membership
access.description: Add a security group to restrict access to the members of that group only. If you add multiple security groups, any member of the groups you have added will have access. Optionally, you may also add a required smart card security group. In that case, the user must be a member of at least one of the configured security groups AND a member of the smartcard security group.
